cat << EOF
This is a work in progress.
This is not dead.

Objectives:
- friendly for the power user, accessible for the new user
- IMAP4rev1, POP3, mbox, mh, NNTP, SMTP (cached and non cached)
- Fast
- I18n (via GTK-2.0 and UTF-8)
- OpenPGP, S/MIME
- Virtual Folders (dynamic folders)
- Extensive search and navigation facilities
- Small footprint, useable also on 640x480 screens
- Modular design:  a possibility to use other GUI toolkits
- Multi-threading
EOF
